<div class="section">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="grid-12 txt-center txt-left-mobile">
      <h2>Creating responsive websites just got a whole lot quicker!</h2>
      <p class="txt--fontSize-m">Amazium 4 has been created to make building your prototype as easy and quick as possible. It includes a ton of modular components from Typography to Forms that will allow you to focus on the more inportant things like your design.</p>
      <ol class="columns columns-3-desktop columns-2-tablet columns-1-mobile">
        <li class="column">
          <img src="img/icon-sass.png" alt="">
          <h3>SCSS &amp; Flexbox</h3>
          <p>Amazium now ships with the popular CSS preprocessor Sass. And as global support for the magical flexbox is over 94% we felt it was time to make the move, and in doing so we can do much more than before in terms of alignment, spacing, ordering and with very little additional code added.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="column">
          <img src="img/icon-grids.png" alt="">
          <h3>Customizable Grid</h3>
          <p>You can set your own parameters as Amazium now uses awesome SCSS to do its grid system which gives you the option to set grid width, column amount and gutter width., Want only 10 columns with 100px gutters sure go for it.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="column">
          <img src="img/icon-stopwatch.png" alt="">
          <h3>Quick Start</h3>
          <p>Amazium now follows the <a href="https://en.bem.info/methodology/" target="_blank">BEM methodology</a> which means we can create extendable and reusable interface components, and as most projects use the same components, code reuse significantly reduces price and time of development.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="column">
          <img src="img/icon-mobile.png" alt="">
          <h3>Mobile First</h3>
          <p>We use the mobile-first approach for styling which means styles are applied first to mobile devices. This in turn means fewer overrides to code for meaning less complicated stylesheets.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="column">
          <img src="img/icon-code.png" alt="">
          <h3>Simple Codebase</h3>
          <p>As were using the BEM methodology all of the styling in Amazium can easily be overrided by your own if needed.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="column">
          <img src="img/icon-box.png" alt="">
          <h3>Smaller than most</h3>
          <p>Amazium is small! Out of the box it's total filesize of every component and class weighs in at a massive ~9KB (gzipped). All you need to worry about now are your massive uncompressed PNG's.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

